HEADWORD: Sprengel pump
<hw>Spreng"el pump`</hw> <pr>(spr⟦ecr⟧ng"⟦eit⟧l p⟦ucr⟧mp`)</pr>.
<fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>A form of air pump in which exhaustion is
produced by a stream of mercury running down a narrow tube, in the
manner of an aspirator; -- named from the inventor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sprent</ent>⟦br⟧
